      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role:</strong> the Deadwatchers — the orc tribe squatting in Scarwall's barbican, the only Belkzen clan hard enough to live beside the curse (they whiten their faces for the ancestor whose flesh blanched fleeing the castle). <strong>Headcount: six warriors</strong> — 1 sentry at A2, 4 in the barracks (A6), 1 at the watch post (A11) — plus @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.urySevenskulls01]{Ury Sevenskulls} (A10). On an alarm they spread to ready bows: 2 to A7, 3 to A8, 1 to A12. <strong>Morale:</strong> to the death while Ury lives; with him dead, each flees below ~15 HP. They never pursue anyone <em>into</em> Scarwall.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
